oc process httpd-example \
-n openshift \
NAME=frontend \
-l app=web \
-o yaml

| Part            | Matlab                                                   |
| --------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| `oc`            | OpenShift CLI                                            |
| `process`       | Template ko process (variable replace) karo              |
| `httpd-example` | Template ka naam                                         |
| `-n openshift`  | Template kis namespace me hai                            |
| `NAME=frontend` | Template ke `${NAME}` variable ki value `frontend` rakho |
| `-l app=web`    | Sab generated resources par `app=web` label add karo     |
| `-o yaml`       | Output YAML format me dikhao                             |

Memory Trick

process ko compiler ki tarah socho:

Template = Source Code
oc process = Compile (variables replace karke final YAML banana)
oc apply = Program execute karna (resources cluster me create/update karna)

Is analogy se process aur apply ka difference hamesha yaad rahega.
